= Thunder Builder =
#context: sop
#type: node

"""Procedurally generates lightning bolt geometry from a polyline."""

== Overview ==

Thunder Builder takes a rest polyline (Input 1) and optionally an animated target line (Input 2), then generates a fractal lightning bolt along the path. Branching, noise, and growth are all fully controllable.

@inputs

Rest Line:
    The base polyline defining the lightning path.

Animated Line To Match:
    An optional animated polyline. When __Match Animated__ is enabled, the bolt follows this line each frame.

@parameters

Match Tip:
    #id: input
    Snaps the tip of the generated bolt to the endpoint of the input line.

Match Animated:
    #id: input2
    Causes the bolt to follow the animated input line (Input 2) each frame. Requires __Match Tip__ to be enabled.

Segments:
    #id: segs
    Total number of segments in the generated bolt.

Growthing:
    #id: growthing
    Growth amount from `0` (no bolt) to `1` (full bolt).

Tail Attrib:
    #id: tail_attr
    Outputs a `tail` point attribute marking the end of each bolt segment.

== Main ==

Noise Type:
    #id: basis
    Noise function used for bolt displacement. Options include Simplex, Perlin, Worley, and others.

Frequency:
    #id: freq
    Noise frequency (XYZ + time).

Offset:
    #id: offset
    Noise offset (XYZ + time).

Fractal Type:
    #id: fractal
    Fractal layering method: None, fBm, Terrain, or Hybrid Terrain.

Roughness:
    #id: rough
    Fractal roughness. Higher values produce more jagged bolts.

Bias Angle:
    #id: val
    Angle bias controlling how much the bolt deviates from the straight path.

Exponent:
    #id: exp
    Sharpens or softens the noise envelope.

Bias Along Curve:
    #id: ramp
    Ramp controlling how much displacement is applied along the length of the bolt.

Angle Sum:
    #id: angle_sum
    When enabled, accumulates displacement angles along the bolt rather than applying them independently.

== Branch ==

Branch:
    #id: branch
    Probability of a branch occurring at each segment.

Max Branch Limited:
    #id: branch_limited
    Maximum number of branches allowed per bolt.

Seed:
    #id: seed
    Random seed for branch placement.

Push Away:
    #id: push_away
    When enabled, branches are pushed away from the main bolt direction instead of using the bias angle.

Branch Root Bias Angle:
    #id: branch_root_bias_angle
    Angle at which branches diverge from the main bolt at their root.

Angle Decrease By Branch Step:
    #id: angle_decrease_by_branch_step
    Reduces the branch angle with each successive branch level.

Bias Angle (Branch):
    #id: bias
    Noise-driven angle bias for branches.

Min/Max Branch Step:
    #id: min_branch_step / max_branch_step
    Range of segment counts between branch points.
